nage Mulitple Favouite WordPress Sites\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/HR8svFX92mU/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:76:\"http://worpit.com/2013/01/manage-mulitple-favouite-wordpress-sites/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 30 Jan 2013 16:42:59 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=3111\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:145:\"With Worpit you can use groups of WordPress sites to better manage them. Select favourites, then refer to them as you perform bulk tasks on them.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3496:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1674\" alt=\"Worpit - Manage Multiple WordPress Sites\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/06/worpit_w.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />A few days ago we told you about our <a title=\"Manage Mutliple WordPress Sites Better with Smart Groups\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2013/01/manage-wordpress-site-smart-groups/\">Smart Groups feature</a> for better management of your WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;ll have noticed in the screenshots for the smart groups the option to list &#8216;Favourite Sites&#8217;.</p>\n<p>What are favourite WordPress sites in Woprit and how do you set them?</p>\n<h2>What is a Favourite Worpit Site?</h2>\n<p>Simply put, a favourite site is one that you have personally marked as a website that stands out from the rest.</p>\n<p>That WordPress site can stand out from the rest for whatever reason, it doesn&#8217;t matter.  What is important, is that it stands out for you.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to mark these sites as favourites, and then to refer to them later in your bulk actions and management of your sites.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-3111\"></span></p>\n<h2>How to mark a WordPress site as a favourite in Worpit</h2>\n<p>When you are reviewing/managing a particular site you&#8217;ll see a little star (<i class=\"icon-star-empty\"></i>) icon beside the name. If this star is yellow, it&#8217;s a favourite, and if it&#8217;s grey, it&#8217;s not.</p>\n<p>Compare the two Worpit screen shots below for one of our sites:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_3113\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-not-favourite-wordpress-site.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-3113\" alt=\"Worpit- A non-favourite WordPress site\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-not-favourite-wordpress-site-300x65.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"65\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Non-favourite</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_3114\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-favourite-wordpress-site-star.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-3114\" alt=\"Worpit- A favourite WordPress Site in Worpit\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-favourite-wordpress-site-star-300x64.png\" width=\"300\" height=\"64\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">A favourite site</p></div>\n<p>To change whether a site is a favourite or not, you simply click on the (<i class=\"icon-star-empty\"></i>).</p>\n<h2>How to use the favourites group to manage your sites</h2>\n<p>So far there are 2 main areas to help you manage just your favourite sites:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Bulk Actions &#8211; where you can perform the same task upon groups of sites without having to even look at them</li>\n<li>All Sites View &#8211; so you can list summaries of your sites to help you get a picture of your WordPress network and what actions need performed.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>You can apply bulk actions to just your favourite sites, or, when selecting your sites to manage, you can list just those sites you&#8217;ve chosen as favourites.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ll be offering many more ways to finely tune your WordPress website groups as the system develops.</p>\n<h2>Get your free Worpit account today</h2>\n<p>Use the link below to sign-up for a free Worpit account and start managing multiple WordPress sites better today!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/HR8svFX92mU\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:72:\"http://worpit.com/2013/01/manage-mulitple-favouite-wordpress-sites/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_b