ir properties.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Paul G.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3062:\"<p></p><p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_focus.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1985\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Manager: Focus\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_focus.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Managing Multiple WordPress sites is a lot of work.</p>\n<p>Services like Worpit are designed and custom built to remove most of this work for you and give you tools to do tasks quickly and efficiently.</p>\n<p>Every little service we add to Worpit is designed to help you do this better.</p>\n<p>One of our latest additions is the concept of &#8216;Smart Groups&#8217; to help you more quickly target the sites you want to manage and review.</p>\n<h2>How do Smart Groups help you manage multiple WordPress sites?</h2>\n<p>It&#8217;s natural to want to group your sites and we recently introduced the 1st stage to making this easier.</p>\n<p>When viewing all the WordPress sites that you  manage, rather than load all of them up every time, it&#8217;s easier to load them in groups, based on certain properties they have.</p>\n<p>For example, some of our smart groups let you focus down on sites with plugins upgrades available, or theme upgrades, or even WordPress Core upgrades.</p>\n<p>See the screen shot below on the currently provided smart groups:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_3101\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 502px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-manage-wordpress-custom-groups.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-3101\" alt=\"Worpit: Manage Multiple WordPress Sites with Smart Groups\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-manage-wordpress-custom-groups.png\" width=\"492\" height=\"369\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Manage Multiple WordPress Sites with Smart Groups</p></div>\n<p>This is just the beginning, and soon you&#8217;ll have the ability to create your own groups and even smart groups.</p>\n<p>To make things a little bit easier, you can now set your default group of sites to load each time your view your sites page. Look for the check box beside the group title:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_3105\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 399px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-manage-wordpress-sites-smart-groups-default.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-3105 \" alt=\"Smart Groups Default Option when managing WordPress Sites with Worpit\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-manage-wordpress-sites-smart-groups-default.png\" width=\"389\" height=\"98\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Smart Groups Default Option</p></div>\n<p>If you&#8217;re not managing WordPress sites using Worpit, you&#8217;re missing out on this cool smart groups feature, and much, much more.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-3098\"></span></p>\n<h2>Get your free Worpit account today</h2>\n<p>Use the link below to sign-up for your free Worpit account and start managing WordPress better today!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/JqLdsSqazFk\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:66:\"http://worpit.com/2013/01/manage-wordpress-site-smart-groups/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/