;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:385:\"We&#8217;re crazy about security at Worpit &#8211; it&#8217;s a ongoing goal to make sure your Worpit is always secured from external access. From the day Worpit launched we&#8217;ve included the option to enable &#8216;Handshaking&#8217; within the Worpit App service. In this article I&#8217;m going to explain more about what &#8216;handshaking&#8217; actually is, and how you [...]\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5700:\"<p></p><p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>We&#8217;re crazy about security at Worpit &#8211; it&#8217;s a ongoing goal to make sure your Worpit is always secured from external access.</p>\n<p>From the day Worpit launched we&#8217;ve included the option to enable &#8216;Handshaking&#8217; within the Worpit App service.</p>\n<p>In this article I&#8217;m going to explain more about what &#8216;handshaking&#8217; actually is, and how you can turn on for all your sites.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-3048\"></span></p>\n<h2>What is Worpit &#8216;Handshaking?</h2>\n<p>Handshaking ensures that all communication sent to the Worpit plugin on your WordPress site has <em>originated</em> from Worpit App.</p>\n<p>What does that mean?</p>\n<p>Simply put, no-one can spoof your plugin.</p>\n<p>Don&#8217;t forget, before anyone can actually send commands to the Worpit plugin in the first place, they&#8217;ll need your secret key and PIN combination.</p>\n<p>This alone ensures communication is legitimate, but we know there are clever people out there that when determined, can overcome some of the most seemingly secure systems.</p>\n<p>Handshaking is another layer that we added to prevent any compromise to your WordPress sites.</p>\n<h3>Worpit Communication <em>With</em> and <em>Without</em> Handshaking Enabled</h3>\n<p>To fully understand the flow between WorpitApp servers and your WordPress website, please read carefully the 2 flow charts below.</p>\n<p>There&#8217;s a lot of writing here, but we&#8217;ve provided details so you have the option to fully understand our communications process if you desire to.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_3050\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 222px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Worpit-comm-no-handshaking.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-3050 \" alt=\"Worpit App and Worpit Plugin Communication Flow without handshaking\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Worpit-comm-no-handshaking-212x300.png\" width=\"212\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Communication flow without handshaking enabled.</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_3058\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 170px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Worpit-comm-with-handshaking.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-3058\" alt=\"WorpitApp Communication with Handshaking Enabled\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Worpit-comm-with-handshaking-160x300.png\" width=\"160\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Communication with Handshaking Enabled</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 style=\"clear: both;\">How to turn on Handshaking for your Worpit WordPress sites</h2>\n<p>Worpit is all about making managing your sites easy!  The effort to perform a task for one site should be equal to the effort to perform the same task for 100 sites.</p>\n<p>Enabling handshaking is no different.</p>\n<p>You can turn-on handshaking for 1 site:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_3076\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 226px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-handshaking-step1.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-3076  \" alt=\"Handshaking Step 1\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-handshaking-step1-300x109.png\" width=\"216\" height=\"78\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Handshaking Step 1</p></div>\n<div id=\"attachment_3077\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 250px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-handshaking-step2.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-3077 \" alt=\"Handshaking Step 2\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/worpit-handshaking-step2-300x174.png\" width=\"240\" height=\"139\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Handshaking Step 2</p></div>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<ol style=\"clear: both;\">\n<li>From the Site screen, click the &#8216;Manage&#8217; button for the site you want to enable Handshaking on.</li>\n<li>Click the &#8216;Extras&#8217; tab menu and open the &#8216;Environment&#8217; section.</li>\n<li>Click the slider to &#8216;Active&#8217; for the Handshaking feature.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>To turn-on handshaking for all, or many of your sites at once:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Click the Bulk Action menu at the top of your Worpit App screen.</li>\n<li>Select the group of sites for which you want to turn handshaking on.</li>\n<li>Then select &#8216;Turn-On Handshaking&#8217;.</li>\n<li>Enter your <a title=\"Increased Worpit Security: Account PIN\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/\">account PIN</a>, and Click &#8216;Go!&#8217;</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Why can&#8217;t you turn on handshaking on some sites</h2>\n<p>Handshaking requires that your WordPress site opens an outgoing web connection to our WorpitApp server.</p>\n<p>This is done using CURL on PHP and some shared web hosting service providers have restricted this ability &#8211; they see enabling this option as a potential for security breach.</p>\n<p>If this is the case for you and your web hosting, it&#8217;s no problem. Worpit will continue to function securely, but you&#8217;ll not be able to add the extra handshaking security layer.</p>\n<h2>Start managing your WordPress Websites today with Worpit.</h2>\n<p>Worpit is free to site up and add your first site. This way you can see the power available when you manage WordPress using Worpit.</p>\n<p>Sign up today, you have nothing to lose, and everything to gain.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/4nwZbTSx3iY\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://worpit.com/2013/01/improve-worpit-security-turning-handshaking/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:70:\"http://worpit.com/2013/01/improve-worpit-security-turning-handshaking/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:3;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"More Easy WordPress Security: Change the WordPress MySQL database user password.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/tgMEixLJOHI/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"http://worpit.com/2012/12/more-easy-wordpress-security-change-wordpress-mysql-database-user-password/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 06 Dec 2012 22:35:53 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2973\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:155:\"Changing the WordPress Database user password is easier than ever, with Worpit. No more editing wp-config or phpMyAdmin. Just give the new password and go!\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3752:\"<p></p><p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>Worpit now has the ability to reset your WordPress MySQL database user password.</p>\n<p>Yes, it&#8217;s that time again: more WordPress security made easy with Worpit!</p>\n<p>This is not something you need to do often, but it&#8217;s one of those things that has 4 or 5 separate steps to it, and that makes automating the task a small joy.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2973\"></span></p>\n<h2>Why would you change the WordPress MySQL Database User Password?</h2>\n<p>You would do this basically for the same reason you rotate any passwords. Security maintenance.</p>\n<p>Using the same password long-term has inherent risks. Regularly updating the password does no harm.</p>\n<p>If at any time you suspect anyone has your WordPress database login credentials, simply changing your password will lock them out.</p>\n<p>The topic of recovering a compromised WordPress site is huge, and I&#8217;ll not go into it here.</p>\n<p>Suffice it to say, there are many things to be done during recovery, and changing the password is one option along the road.</p>\n<h2>What does changing the WordPress MySQL Database User Password involve?</h2>\n<p>There are 2 main steps involved here.</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Change the password for the MySQL database user.</li>\n<li>Update the WordPress wp-config.php with the new MySQL password</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Neither of these are difficult, but can be a little time consuming if you have many sites you need to perform this on.</p>\n<p>This is where Worpit helps as it provides an interface to directly making these changes without you having to do any of the heavy lifting.</p>\n<h2>How to change the WordPress MySQL Password the easy way: Worpit</h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_2994\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 498px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/worpit-reset-wordpress-mysql-database-password1.png\"><img class=\" wp-image-2994 \" title=\"Worpit: Reset WordPress MySQL Database User Password\" alt=\"Worpit: Reset WordPress MySQL Database User Password\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/12/worpit-reset-wordpress-mysql-database-password1.png\" width=\"488\" height=\"152\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Easily reset WordPress Database Password using Worpit</p></div>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy to update your MySQL user password with Worpit. You simply supply the new password, confirm you&#8217;re ready to do it, and click the button.</p>\n<p>This feature may not work if you have 2 security settings in place, namely:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>PHP cannot write to your wp-config.php file, and/or</li>\n<li>PHP cannot use the exec to make system calls</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If your system doesn&#8217;t support it, it wont make the change and will leave your site intact. That said though, it&#8217;s always important to have a backup of your database and wp-config.php file.</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit WordPress Advantage today</h2>\n<p>Managing all your WordPress websites is fun again with Worpit. You can perform many different WordPress management tasks to do with plugins, themes, security, and more.</p>\n<p>Best of all, you can perform them in bulk across all your sites.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s never been easier to manage all your WordPress sites &#8211; and it&#8217;s <a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress Websites With Worpit!\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/dashboard/signup\" target=\"_blank\">free to sign-up and get started</a>!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/tgMEixLJOHI\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:106:\"http://worpit.com/2012/12/more-easy-wordpress-security-change-wordpress-mysql-database-user-password/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"http://worpit.com/2012/12/more-easy-wordpress-security-change-wordpress-mysql-database-user-password/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:4;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:61:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup: A few common pre-signup questions\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/-WXPjVzav54/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-common-pre-signup-questions/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 29 Nov 2012 16:34:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WorpDrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2964\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"A few common questions answered about the WorpDrive WordPress Backup and Recovery service.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:3615:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2522\" title=\"WorpDrive: Automated WordPress Backup\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/WorpDrive-WordPress-Backup-Logo-200px.png\" alt=\"WorpDrive: Automated WordPress Backup\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />Yesterday we launched <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup</a> to the public, on our Worpit platform.</p>\n<p>So far so great!</p>\n<p>It turns out lots of people have been waiting for its release and the response we&#8217;ve received has been positive and a little overwhelming.</p>\n<p>Here are some of the most common questions we&#8217;ve had&#8230;</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2964\"></span></p>\n<h3 class=\"clear\">1. What is the space limit on WorpDrive for 1 site?</h3>\n<p>There is no space limit for WorpDrive.</p>\n<p>One WorpDrive license provides 1GB storage space. If you exceed this space, the system will automatically increment your WorpDrive licenses by 1, thereby adding an extra 1GB space.</p>\n<h3>2. Can I share my disk space between sites if one has more than 1GB and one has less.</h3>\n<p>Yes. The total disk quota in WorpDrive is shared. So if you have 3 WorpDrive licenses, you have a total of 3GB backup space that can be used by those 3 websites.</p>\n<h3>3. What technology does WorpDrive use? How does it work?</h3>\n<p>WorpDrive uses lots of different technology, and a lot of in-house custom-built software to run.  It doesn&#8217;t use <em>any WordPress code</em> to do what it does.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s fundamentally a combination of FTP and <a title=\"Subversion (SVN)\" href=\"http://subversion.apache.org/\" target=\"_blank\">SVN</a>.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive creates a replica of your website, and does a dump of your WordPress database. Then it adds all this to a new SVN repository.</p>\n<h3>4. How long does WorpDrive activation take?  It seems to take a long time&#8230;</h3>\n<p>This is expected. WorpDrive activation is dependent on 2 main factors:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>How big your site is. The bigger it is, the longer it will take to replicate and then add to the respository.</li>\n<li>Where your site is in the queue. We have a first-in-first-out activation queue as we don&#8217;t want to overload our infrastructure. Your site will be processed when it&#8217;s next up in the queue.</li>\n</ol>\n<h3>5. How long would backups take if activation takes a long time?</h3>\n<p>Backups are only capturing the changes and should happen relatively very quickly.</p>\n<h3>6. Is Worpit included with WorpDrive, or the other way about?</h3>\n<p>No. Think of Worpit as the platform upon which you manage all your WordPress sites in one place.</p>\n<p>Then consider WorpDrive as the website backup component of your management tasks.</p>\n<p>At the moment, you must have Worpit to use WorpDrive&#8230; that will probably change in the future.</p>\n<p>Worpit licenses are completely independent of WorpDrive licenses.</p>\n<h2>Any more questions?</h2>\n<p>If you have any questions or suggestions, please feel free to contact us either directly from within Worpit itself, or <a title=\"Contact Worpit\" href=\"http://worpit.com/help-support/contact/\">on the website</a>.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re more than happy to get your feedback, and help you if you have any issues or want more information.</p>\n<p>If you want to try Worpit, you can <a title=\"Worpit App: Manage Multiple WordPress Websites\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/signup\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up today for free here</a>.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/-WXPjVzav54\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:86:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-common-pre-signup-questions/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:81:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-common-pre-signup-questions/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:5;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup: Ultra-Reliable WordPress backup is available for all\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/HA4KkUBPEuE/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-ultra-reliable-wordpress-backup/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 28 Nov 2012 12:56:09 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WorpDrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2922\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:156:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup is live and available for everyone. Finally, ultra-reliable WordPress Backup is within reach of all website owners big and small.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4919:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-2522\" title=\"WorpDrive: Ultra-Reliable WordPress Backup\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/WorpDrive-WordPress-Backup-Logo-200px.png\" alt=\"WorpDrive: Ultra-Reliable WordPress Backup\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />Today Worpit has released WorpDrive WordPress Backup.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive is an <em>all-new approach</em> to WordPress data protection and recovery.</p>\n<p>It is built to be highly reliable, cloud-based, and available to all website owners big and small.</p>\n<div class=\"alert alert-info clear\">WorpDrive is currently on promotion for a <strong>limited launch offer</strong>. All sites are £2.00 / €2,50 / US$3.00 with 1GB storage. The price you pay today is the price you always pay.</div>\n<h2>What is WorpDrive?</h2>\n<p>WorpDrive is super-charged WordPress Backup and Recovery.</p>\n<p>Some of the great features WorpDrive offers as standard &#8230;</p>\n<ol style=\"list-style-position: outside;\">\n<li>Never worry about backups again &#8211; it&#8217;s completely <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #1 – Complete Automation\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-1-complete-automation/\" target=\"_blank\">automatic WordPress Backup</a>.</li>\n<li>Security &#8211; all data is <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #2 – Ultimate WordPress Backup Security\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-2-ultimate-backup-security/\" target=\"_blank\">securely encrypted, and is WordPress-<strong>independent</strong></a>.</li>\n<li>You can test every backup &#8211; WorpDrive lets you <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #3 – Proof That Your Backup Actually Works\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-3-proof-your-backup-works/\" target=\"_blank\">test that your WordPress backup works</a>.</li>\n<li>You can <em><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #4 – Reveal The Mystery Inside Your Backups\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-4-reveal-mystery-inside-backups/\" target=\"_blank\">see inside your WordPress backups</a></em> &#8211; WorpDrive lets you see precisely the files that have changed and their contents.</li>\n<li><strong>Stress-Free WordPress Backups &#8211; <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #5 – No more stress, Reliable WordPress Backup\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive just works</a>.</strong></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive Features and Benefits\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com/worpdrive-benefits/\" target=\"_blank\">more&#8230;</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p><span id=\"more-2922\"></span></p>\n<h2>How does WorpDrive work?</h2>\n<p>WorpDrive is far cleverer than traditional backup services that use clunky ZIPs and WordPress plugins.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive WordPress Backup only copies the changes that have happened on your site. It doesn&#8217;t copy everything, every time &#8211; that&#8217;s a waste.</p>\n<p>Using technology that professional software developers use, we have been able to build a system designed to work specifically with your WordPress website.</p>\n<p>And the result is a WordPress Backup system that is un-matched in speed, features, and reliability.</p>\n<h2>How can you get WorpDrive?</h2>\n<p>Easy!</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Signup for your <a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress websites with Worpit\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/welcome/?src=worpdrive-launch\" target=\"_blank\">free Worpit account here</a>.</li>\n<li>Add a website to your Worpit account</li>\n<li>Test it for <a title=\"Get WorpDrive WordPress Backup Compatible\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com/get-worpdrive-compatibility/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive compatibility</a></li>\n<li>Activate WorpDrive WordPress Backup</li>\n<li>Relax</li>\n<li>(If you need more, subscribe to more Worpit sites and then activate WorpDrive on them)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>WorpDrive is designed to be as simple, and as user-friendly as possible.</p>\n<p>You don&#8217;t even need to setup Amazon S3, or Dropbox, or any other storage provider. This is all handled for you.</p>\n<h2>What makes WorpDrive extra special? &#8211; the Worpit Advantage.</h2>\n<p>WorpDrive is built into Worpit &#8211; an all-in-one WordPress Management System.</p>\n<p>Worpit is custom built for you, to make your WordPress life easier.</p>\n<p>So now, not only can you manage the plugins, themes, security, and updates for your all your WordPress website in 1 place, you can manage their regular backup and recovery too.</p>\n<p>Worpit is free to start and you can <a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress websites with Worpit\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/signup\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up here any time</a>. No credit cards, no billing information, just a free account.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/HA4KkUBPEuE\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-ultra-reliable-wordpress-backup/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-ultra-reliable-wordpress-backup/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:6;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:38:\"Increased Worpit Security: Account PIN\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/oHMduAPM0Vc/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 26 Nov 2012 14:47:51 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"WordPress News and Updates\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2892\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:155:\"All sensitive Worpit features are protected by a second layer of security: Account PIN. It\'s easy to setup and easy to use. Here, we explain more about it.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:4973:\"<p></p><p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\"><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" /></a>At Worpit, our goal is to help you do more, in less time, with your WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>At the same time, <a title=\"Worpit Security: How does Worpit handle security of your WordPress site and your data?\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/07/worpit-security-how-worpit-handle-security-wordpress-data/\">security</a> is a <a title=\"Worpit Now Enforces Secure SSL\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/07/worpit-enforces-secure-ssl/\">top priority</a> <a title=\"How does Worpit handle security of client financial data?\" href=\"http://worpit.com/faq/how-does-worpit-handle-security-of-client-financial-transactions/\">for Worpit</a>.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;re constantly improving our systems to ensure all data is secure and protected.</p>\n<p>And today we&#8217;ve released an update to protect you further: Account PINs.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2892\"></span></p>\n<h2>What is the Worpit Account PIN?</h2>\n<p>We know that typing in a password every time you want to do something can be a serious pain.</p>\n<p>Of course, you must always log into your Worpit account using your password, but we&#8217;ve now added the ability to create an account PIN.</p>\n<p>This PIN will protect certain Worpit features on your WordPress sites.</p>\n<p>For example, Worpit lets you log into all your WordPress sites with the click of a button.  We think this feature should have an extra layer of protection.</p>\n<p>If we were to protect it with your account password, we see 3 potential problems:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>you&#8217;re might decide to chose a less-secure account password that&#8217;s easier to remember, or</li>\n<li>you use a password manager to remember your password &#8211; if someone gets access to your browser or your manager, you&#8217;re in trouble, or</li>\n<li>typing in your password makes the service so user-<strong>unfriendly</strong> that you wont use it. And that would make us sad <img src=\'http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_sad.gif\' alt=\':(\' class=\'wp-smiley\' /> </li>\n</ol>\n<p>This is why the Account PIN has been created &#8211; you can chose a PIN number of at least 4 digits and use this to access certain restricted features on your Worpit account.</p>\n<p>That way, there is no big password to remember, and all sensitive account features are protected by a <strong>second security layer</strong>.</p>\n<p>Win &#8211; Win!</p>\n<h2>How does the secure PIN feature work?</h2>\n<p>It&#8217;s easy.  If you haven&#8217;t set a PIN, you&#8217;ll just enter your account password where prompted to do so.</p>\n<p>To setup your PIN, go to your <a title=\"Worpit App Account Profile\" href=\"https://worpitapp.com/dashboard/profile\" target=\"_blank\">Account Profile in Worpit</a>, then select the &#8216;Password and PIN&#8217; tab.</p>\n<p>Enter your existing account password (the PIN cannot be set without this) in the first box, and supply your PIN (as seen in the screen-shot below).</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2894\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-password-and-pin.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2894 \" title=\"Worpit Password and PIN\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-password-and-pin-300x182.png\" alt=\"Worpit Password and PIN\" width=\"300\" height=\"182\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Worpit Password and PIN</p></div>\n<p>Once this PIN has been set, each time you try to access a Worpit feature that we feel is sensitive enough to require a PIN, you will be prompted to enter it:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2897\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-enter-password-pin-dialog.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2897\" title=\"Worpit: Enter Password or PIN dialog\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/worpit-enter-password-pin-dialog-300x134.png\" alt=\"Worpit: Enter Password or PIN dialog\" width=\"300\" height=\"134\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Worpit: Enter Password or PIN prompt</p></div>\n<p>We feel this greatly enhances and complements Worpit&#8217;s growing list of security features and protections.</p>\n<p>There are more planned, but we trust that our efforts so far indicate how much importance we place on your account data and its security.</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today</h2>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/oHMduAPM0Vc\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:64:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/increased-worpit-security-account-pin/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #5 – No more stress, Reliable WordPress Backup\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/fGmiygbcXSw/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:114:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Sun, 25 Nov 2012 13:16:57 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"WorpDrive\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2833\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:150:\"WorpDrive offers you no-more-stress WordPress Backup and Recovery system. It takes control of your daily backups, so you don\'t have to worry any more.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6454:\"<p></p><div id=\"attachment_2861\" class=\"wp-caption alignright\" style=\"width: 235px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/stress-free-wordpress-backup.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-2861 \" title=\"WorpDrive is stress-free WordPress Backup\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/stress-free-wordpress-backup-225x300.jpg\" alt=\"WorpDrive is stress-free WordPress Backup\" width=\"225\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">WorpDrive is stress-free WordPress Backup</p></div>\n<p>Can you imagine the feeling of knowing all your WordPress websites are protected with a reliable WordPress backup service?</p>\n<p>Take a moment and think of all those frustrating little things you&#8217;d never have to do again (for every site!).</p>\n<p>How is WorpDrive different?</p>\n<p>WorpDrive is <strong>reliable</strong>.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2833\"></span></p>\n<h2 class=\"clear\">WorpDrive is different: it&#8217;s <em>reliable </em>WordPress Backup</h2>\n<p>Have you ever bought a backup service and it doesn&#8217;t work on your web hosting?</p>\n<p>Snap.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve all been there.</p>\n<p>Do you&#8230;</p>\n<ul>\n<li>get &#8220;PHP FATAL out of memory errors&#8221; with your backup plugin?</li>\n<li>have problems copying to Dropbox / S3 / &lt;<em>fill in your storage provider here</em>&gt; ?</li>\n<li>use lots of space on your server storing zip files of old backups?</li>\n<li>contact the author of the plugin explaining how your backup doesn&#8217;t work?</li>\n<li>search Google and support forums looking for people with the same problems as you?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>You&#8217;re not alone.</p>\n<p>This is considered &#8220;normal&#8221; for WordPress backups.</p>\n<p>We decided to take a bold new approach to backing up your websites, something that was seemingly never thought of before:</p>\n<blockquote><p><strong>we wanted to remove all stress and frustration from WordPress backups for good</strong>.</p></blockquote>\n<p>We have built WorpDrive to be super-reliable WordPress backup. This has taken a lot of hard work, but we&#8217;ve finally made it.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive has a few special requirements that you must have on your web hosting before it will work.</p>\n<p>But the cool thing about WorpDrive, is that we wont let you activate it unless your website meets these requirements, and passes the compatibility tests with flying colours.</p>\n<p>Why?</p>\n<p>Because we know how frustrating it is to buy a backup product and discover you have nothing but problems with it.</p>\n<p>Sure, the problems might be because of your web hosting, or your WordPress configuration, or your PHP setup&#8230; doesn&#8217;t matter, it&#8217;s still frustrating.</p>\n<p>If your website passes the compatibility tests, it&#8217;ll run WorpDrive without any issues. You can then be confident that your sites are backed-up and <a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #3 – Proof That Your Backup Actually Works\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-3-proof-your-backup-works/\">ready to be recovered the moment</a> you need it.</p>\n<h2>What makes WorpDrive such a reliable WordPress Backup?</h2>\n<p>Your WordPress site is basically a software program.</p>\n<p>It&#8217;s constantly changing because you update plugins, themes and WordPress.</p>\n<p>WorpDrive backup system uses technology that software development companies use to manage their software.</p>\n<p>And why not? Why shouldn&#8217;t you take advantage of the same tools that developers use, to keep your WordPress site protected?</p>\n<p>WorpDrive has gone through many development phases before we deemed it good enough to be ready for you.</p>\n<p>We didn&#8217;t rush it out, trying to make quick money off sales.</p>\n<p>We tested, tested, and tested some more. Our beta testers can testify to this (thank you beta testers!).</p>\n<h2>Are your websites ready for reliable WordPress Backups?</h2>\n<p>If you <a title=\"Worpit App: Manage Multiple WordPress Websites\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">sign-up to Worpit today</a> (for free) you can start testing your websites to see if they&#8217;re ready.</p>\n<p>If you discover they&#8217;re not ready for WorpDrive, we&#8217;ll tell you what the problem is and you can ask your web host to help you fix the issues.</p>\n<p>The requirements aren&#8217;t crazy, and most quality web hosting companies will support WorpDrive. We&#8217;ll soon have a list of recommended web hosts to help you find compatible web hosting.</p>\n<h2>Why is WorpDrive not free?</h2>\n<p>Some people contact us expecting WorpDrive to be a part of Worpit and wonder why the backup system isn&#8217;t free.</p>\n<p>If you believe you can find a backup system that is free or even costs the same as WorpDrive and has all the features listed below, we&#8217;d like to know about it:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #1 – Complete Automation\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-1-complete-automation/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup is completely automatic</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #2 – Ultimate WordPress Backup Security\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-2-ultimate-backup-security/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup is secure</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #3 – Proof That Your Backup Actually Works\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-3-proof-your-backup-works/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup gives you proof that every backup works</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup Features #4 – Reveal The Mystery Inside Your Backups\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/10/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-4-reveal-mystery-inside-backups/\" target=\"_blank\">WorpDrive WordPress Backup lets you see inside every backup</a></li>\n<li><a title=\"WorpDrive WordPress Backup and Recovery Features\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com/worpdrive-benefits/\" target=\"_blank\">Many more features</a>&#8230;</li>\n</ol>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today!</h2>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/fGmiygbcXSw\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:110:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:105:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/worpdrive-wordpress-backup-features-5-no-more-stress-reliable-wordpress-backup/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:59:\"Secure WordPress Login and Admin Dashboard with SSL (HTTPS)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/TuHLnhBUov0/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:84:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/secure-wordpress-login-admin-dashboard-ssl-https/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Wed, 21 Nov 2012 11:27:44 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16:\"WordPress Guides\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2763\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:155:\"Force SSL Admin and Force SSL Login are easy WordPress security features to set. All you need is an SSL certificate on your site and to follow this how-to.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12:\"Worpit Admin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7954:\"<p></p><p><img class=\"alignleft size-full wp-image-1751\" title=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/07/worpit_w_padlock.png\" alt=\"Worpit WordPress Security\" width=\"200\" height=\"200\" />One of Worpit&#8217;s goals is to help you make all your WordPress websites more secure.</p>\n<p>Implementing good security principles isn&#8217;t difficult, but it&#8217;ll take you a long time to do on each site.</p>\n<p>So far we&#8217;ve shown you that Worpit can help keep your websites more secure by:</p>\n<ol style=\"clear: both;\">\n<li>regularly <a title=\"More WordPress Security: WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-wordpress-authentication-keys-salts/\">resetting the WordPress Authentication Keys and Salts</a>.</li>\n<li><a title=\"Changing the WordPress Database Table Prefix, Security through Obscurity\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/changing-wordpress-database-table-prefix-security-obscurity/\">renaming your WordPress database table prefix</a> to something other than the default.</li>\n<li><a title=\"More WordPress Security: Disallow File Edit Setting In WordPress\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/more-wordpress-security-disallow-file-edit-setting-wordpress/\">disabling the ability to edit files</a> from within the WordPress dashboard.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>These are serious security advantages that reduce your surface area to attack.</p>\n<p>Worpit lets you put these protections in place with just a click of a button.</p>\n<p>WordPress has another useful option to sure-up your websites: SSL / HTTPS.</p>\n<p>By the end of this article you&#8217;ll understand all you need to know about enabling SSL or HTTPS on your WordPress admin, and of course how to do it.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2763\"></span></p>\n<h2>What&#8217;s the 1st thing you need to know about WordPress Admin and SSL?</h2>\n<p>The basic requirement for secure SSL logins to WordPress, and a secure SSL-based admin area, is the <em>presence of an SSL certificate</em>.</p>\n<p>If your website doesn&#8217;t have this, it&#8217;s not going to work.</p>\n<p>But all is not lost.. it is possible to use your web hosting control panel, or to ask your web host if you&#8217;re unsure how this is done, to create a &#8220;self-signed&#8221; SSL certificate.</p>\n<p>The self-signed certificate is only for website admin and not for any other purpose &#8211; if you enable SSL on your whole WordPress site you&#8217;re going to have a few issues with your visitors.</p>\n<p>Enabling SSL on a website is a much bigger topic than can be covered in this article, but I&#8217;ll assume that if you read on, you have a valid SSL certificate installed, whether certified/signed by a root certificate authority, or just self-signed.</p>\n<h2>WordPress Security Option 1: Force <em>Login</em> Over SSL</h2>\n<p>With this option enabled, the WordPress login is always <strong>forced</strong> over SSL.  That means the URL for submitting the login form will begin with <code>HTTPS://</code></p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have an SSL certificate installed on your site (as mentioned earlier) you&#8217;ll face login problems so only do this if you&#8217;ve sorted this part out first.</p>\n<p>Since WordPress normally login runs over unsecured HTTP:// connections, usernames and passwords are sent as clear text and easily readable by someone who is looking closely at the traffic.</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2823\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 310px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/force-ssl-login-form-source-wordpress.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2823\" title=\"Force SSL Login Form for WordPress\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/force-ssl-login-form-source-wordpress-300x30.png\" alt=\"Force SSL Login Form for WordPress\" width=\"300\" height=\"30\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Force SSL Login Form for WordPress</p></div>\n<p>With this option enabled, the problem of snooping is averted and you have a secure channel for submitting WordPress login information.</p>\n<p>After this is enabled, you&#8217;ll know it&#8217;s working when you look at the source of your login form page (see image).</p>\n<h2>WordPress Security Option 2: Force <em>Admin</em> Over SSL</h2>\n<p>When this option is enabled, it <strong>forces</strong> the whole of the WordPress Admin area (including logins and registrations) to be served with SSL &#8211; i.e. over HTTPS.</p>\n<p>This is the most ideal solution in terms of a secure connection, but again, you&#8217;ll need to have an SSL certificate installed for that site.</p>\n<h2>How to enable the FORCE_SSL security options on your WordPress sites &#8211; the easy way</h2>\n<div id=\"attachment_2765\" class=\"wp-caption alignleft\" style=\"width: 357px\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2765 \" title=\"Force SSL Admin / Login for WordPress\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/force-ssl-admin-login-wordpress.png\" alt=\"Force SSL Admin / Login for WordPress\" width=\"347\" height=\"71\" /><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Force SSL Admin / Login for WordPress</p></div>\n<p>As you probably know by now, Worpit is by far the easiest way to manage many of your WordPress security options.</p>\n<p>All you do is flick the switch, and Worpit will go off and make the necessary changes for you on each of your sites.</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t have a Worpit account, or you don&#8217;t want to sign-up for the free one (that includes these security tools as standard), then you can follow the how-to guide below.</p>\n<h2>How to enable the FORCE_SSL options within WordPress &#8211; the hard way</h2>\n<p>When you use Worpit to set this setting, you can turn it on and off quickly.</p>\n<p>This is useful if 99% of the time you don&#8217;t use the editor, but sometimes you want to just quickly make an edit. Worpit can let you turn off the setting, and then re-enable it as soon as you&#8217;re done.</p>\n<p>But, if you want to do it manually, it&#8217;s easy. Here&#8217;s how:</p>\n<h4>1. Make a backup of your wp-config.php file.</h4>\n<p>If you&#8217;re using a <a title=\"WordPress Backup and Recovery\" href=\"http://worpdrive.com\" target=\"_blank\">WordPress backup system like WorpDrive</a>, just fire off a backup, wait until it&#8217;s completed and continue on.</p>\n<h4>2. Open up your wp-config.php file for editing.</h4>\n<p>Download the <code>wp-config.php</code> from your website and open it up in your favourite text editor</p>\n<h4>3. Find the setting FORCE_SSL_LOGIN in your wp-config.php and change it to true</h4>\n<p>By default, this setting is not specified in the WordPress wp-config.php file. If you&#8217;ve never set this before, it wont be there, and you&#8217;ll have to add it yourself.</p>\n<p>But you need to be careful where you add new configuration settings &#8211; you cannot add them to the end of the file.</p>\n<p>A good place to do it is after the line that sets <code>WP_DEBUG</code>.</p>\n<p>To enable this security setting, add the following line to your wp-config.php:</p>\n<pre>define( \'FORCE_SSL_LOGIN\', true );</pre>\n<h4>4. Repeat step 3 but for FORCE_SSL_ADMIN</h4>\n<p>Simply do what you did for step 3, but use this line:</p>\n<pre>define( \'FORCE_SSL_ADMIN\', true );</pre>\n<h4>5. Replace your wp-config.php</h4>\n<p>Save your <code>wp-config.php</code> file with the changes, and upload it back to your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>You&#8217;re done!</p>\n<h2>Get the Worpit Advantage Today &#8211; Free</h2>\n<p>This setting is also not a difficult security tasks, but made much easier when using Worpit if you have many websites to manage and maintain.</p>\n<p>Worpit lets you manage your plugins, themes, and security (and much more) across all your WordPress websites from one convenient, secure, dashboard.</p>\n<p>And it’s free to signup. No commitments, no credit cards.</p>\n<p>Just good WordPress management.</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/TuHLnhBUov0\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:80:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/secure-wordpress-login-admin-dashboard-ssl-https/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:75:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/secure-wordpress-login-admin-dashboard-ssl-https/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:42:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:6:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:92:\"Lesson: Never be afraid to change your web host when they’re not performing as they should\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:53:\"http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/Worpit/~3/LVPY-nBUxDc/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:94:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/lesson-never-be-afraid-change-web-host-when-performing-bad/#comments\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Tue, 20 Nov 2012 19:47:24 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Worpit: Manage WordPress Better\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:25:\"http://worpit.com/?p=2780\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:144:\"Who you host your WordPress sites with makes all the difference. Never be afraid to switch to something better. Here is a perfect example why...\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:7:\"Paul G.\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:5308:\"<p></p><p>A couple of days ago Worpit received a tweet about our website being down.</p>\n<p><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/tweet-worpit-site-down.png\"><img class=\"size-full wp-image-2781 aligncenter\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px;\" title=\"Tweet: Worpit Website Down\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/tweet-worpit-site-down.png\" alt=\"Tweet: Worpit Website Down\" width=\"535\" height=\"110\" /></a></p>\n<p>That&#8217;s not something you want to wake up to in the morning.</p>\n<p>If you&#8217;re a small start-up business like us, you need all the up-time you can get.</p>\n<p>So I set to work to see if I could pin-point the problem and try to fix it.</p>\n<p><span id=\"more-2780\"></span></p>\n<h2>Web hosting problems are usually because of your web host</h2>\n<p>We take great care when we update our websites, and I hadn&#8217;t updated any of the Worpit site in the past 24-48hrs so I suspected it wasn&#8217;t a site coding issue.</p>\n<p>It was either down to 1 of 2 things.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"http://www.cloudflare.com\" target=\"_blank\">Cloudflare</a>, or</li>\n<li>our web host &#8211; <a title=\"VPS.net cloud hosting\" href=\"http://bit.ly/MZWsZ0\" target=\"_blank\">VPS.net</a></li>\n</ol>\n<p>We use <a title=\"CloudFlare – Boost your WordPress site security and performance in 10 minutes\" href=\"http://worpit.com/2012/08/cloudflare-boost-wordpress-security-performance/\" target=\"_blank\">cloudflare to help secure and improve our websites&#8217; performance</a>. It normally works excellent, but sometimes it takes a hit and our sites go a bit funky. Much less so now it has to be said.</p>\n<p>Turned out Cloudflare didn&#8217;t have any outages that would have affected our site around the time this tweet was posted so I ruled them out pretty quick.</p>\n<p>I then checked the error logs and it turned out that on several occasions the:</p>\n<pre>MySQL server has gone away</pre>\n<p>error was appearing in the logs much too often.</p>\n<p>This basically meant that the MySQL server for worpit.com was basically timing out &#8211; a connection was opened, and a request was made but no response from the MySQL process.</p>\n<p>We made the decision from the beginning to use a dedicated cloud hosting service from VPS.net for the Worpit.com website. In this way it would never be affected by issues that could affect the worpitapp.com service.</p>\n<p>We&#8217;ve had a few quirks with the hosting, but nothing crazy. On the whole it&#8217;s performed well enough.</p>\n<h2><em>Only that which is measured can be improved</em> &#8211; especially true of server  up-time and response time</h2>\n<p>I decided to start monitoring the Worpit site over a couple of days to see how it was doing.</p>\n<p>The tool I used to do this was <a title=\"Pingdom website monitoring\" href=\"http://www.pingdom.com\" target=\"_blank\">Pingdom.com</a>.</p>\n<p>This horrific result was this:</p>\n<div id=\"attachment_2795\" class=\"wp-caption aligncenter\" style=\"width: 238px\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-uptime-report-worpitcom.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2795\" title=\"Pingdom Uptime Report: Worpit.com\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-uptime-report-worpitcom-228x300.png\" alt=\"Pingdom Uptime Report: Worpit.com\" width=\"228\" height=\"300\" /></a><p class=\"wp-caption-text\">Pingdom Uptime Report: Worpit.com</p></div>\n<p>Clearly this doesn&#8217;t inspire confidence.</p>\n<p>I decided not to wait for the 24~48hrs I had initially planned, and set about moving the website to alternative hosting.</p>\n<p>Within an hour I had moved both worpit.com and worpdrive.com to one of our <a title=\"VPS Hosting with TMZ\" href=\"http://bit.ly/XxU7M3\" target=\"_blank\">servers hosted with TMZVPS.com</a>.</p>\n<p>Since the move, worpit.com has been offline once, and we got a great boost in server response time which increased on average by a factor of around 10x (see image below).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-response-time-chart-worpitcom.png\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-2797 aligncenter\" title=\"Pingdom Response Time Chart: Worpit.com\" src=\"http://worpit.com/wrdp/wp-content/uploads/2012/11/pingdom-response-time-chart-worpitcom-300x203.png\" alt=\"Pingdom Response Time Chart: Worpit.com\" width=\"300\" height=\"203\" /></a></p>\n<h2>Who you host your sites with makes all the difference</h2>\n<p>Don&#8217;t think that because you&#8217;re hosting with a big name, and they come highly recommend you should stick with them even when their performance is crappy.</p>\n<p>Who you host with is entirely up to you and it doesn&#8217;t matter who recommended them to you.</p>\n<p>Yes, it can be a pain to move your web hosting to another provider, but with the right setup from the start, and the right tools, it&#8217;s easy.</p>\n<p>Worpit will soon be releasing WordPress cloning and site migration tools so stay tuned.</p>\n<p>If you want to hear of new features as they&#8217;re released, sign-up for your free Worpit account.</p>\n<p><a title=\"Manage Multiple WordPress Websites with Worpit\" href=\"http://worpitapp.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Get the Worpit Advantage</a> today!</p>\n<img src=\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/~r/Worpit/~4/LVPY-nBUxDc\" height=\"1\" width=\"1\"/>\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:90:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/lesson-never-be-afraid-change-web-host-when-performing-bad/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:8:\"origLink\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:85:\"http://worpit.com/2012/11/lesson-never-be-afraid-change-web-host-when-performing-bad/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:44:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\";a:2:{s:12:\"updatePeriod\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:6:\"hourly\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:15:\"updateFrequency\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"1\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:2:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:3:{s:3:\"rel\";s:4:\"self\";s:4:\"type\";s:19:\"application/rss+xml\";s:4:\"href\";s:34:\"http://feeds.feedburner.com/Worpit\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:2:{s:3:\"rel\";s:3:\"hub\";s:4:\"href\";s:32:\"http://pubsubhubbub.appspot.com/\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:42:\"http://rssnamespace.org/feedburner/ext/1.0\";a:1:{s:4:\"info\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:3:\"uri\";s:6:\"worpit\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}}}}}}s:4:\"type\";i:128;s:7:\"headers\";a:9:{s:12:\"content-type\";s:23:\"text/xml; charset=UTF-8\";s:4:\"etag\";s:27:\"E1vooj5jAqevNI6Yle98fg/qAD0\";s:13:\"last-modified\";s:29:\"Sun, 03 Feb 2013 07:45:32 GMT\";s:4:\"date\";s:29:\"Sun, 03 Feb 2013 08:54:38 GMT\";s:7:\"expires\";s:29:\"Sun, 03 Feb 2013 08:54:38 GMT\";s:13:\"cache-control\";s:18:\"private, max-age=0\";s:22:\"x-content-type-options\";s:7:\"nosniff\";s:16:\"x-xss-protection\";s:13:\"1; mode=block\";s:6:\"server\";s:3:\"GSE\";}s:5:\"build\";s:14:\"20130109003921\";}','no'),
